.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH cdf 1  "cdf 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
cdf \- Plan, run, and inspect governed data movement
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcdf\fR [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-unicode\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Plan, run, and inspect governed data movement with durable packages, checkpoints, receipts, and schema evidence.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress progress and non\-primary success narration
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show evidence detail; repeat for diagnostics
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Color policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Progress policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-unicode\fR \fI<WHEN>\fR
Unicode policy: auto, always, or never
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
cdf\-help(1)
Show help for a command
.TP
cdf\-version(1)
Print the cdf version
.TP
cdf\-init(1)
Create a new cdf project
.TP
cdf\-add(1)
Add a source resource to the project
.TP
cdf\-validate(1)
Validate project configuration and contracts
.TP
cdf\-plan(1)
Plan a resource run without executing it
.TP
cdf\-explain(1)
Explain resolution, capabilities, and execution choices
.TP
cdf\-run(1)
Execute a governed resource run
.TP
cdf\-preview(1)
Read a bounded preview without committing data
.TP
cdf\-sql(1)
Query cdf system metadata
.TP
cdf\-inspect(1)
Inspect durable project and run evidence
.TP
cdf\-diff(1)
Compare durable schemas
.TP
cdf\-schema(1)
Discover, pin, compare, and promote schemas
.TP
cdf\-contract(1)
Freeze, show, and test contracts
.TP
cdf\-state(1)
Inspect and recover checkpoint state
.TP
cdf\-resume(1)
Resume interrupted work from the run ledger
.TP
cdf\-replay(1)
Replay a verified package
.TP
cdf\-backfill(1)
Plan or execute a bounded cursor backfill
.TP
cdf\-package(1)
List, verify, archive, and collect packages
.TP
cdf\-doctor(1)
Check local runtime and destination health
.TP
cdf\-status(1)
Summarize project freshness and run state
.SH EXTRA
Environment:
  CDF_PROJECT       Project directory or cdf.toml path
  CDF_ENV           Project environment name
  CDF_TARGET        Default destination
  NO_COLOR          Disable color unless \-\-color always is explicit
  CLICOLOR_FORCE    Request color when output is interactive
  COLUMNS           Width fallback when terminal size is unavailable

Examples:
  cdf validate
  cdf plan local.events \-\-to duckdb://.cdf/dev.duckdb
  cdf run local.events \-v
  cdf inspect run RUN_ID
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
